WorldStage Newsonline– The Commissioner for the Accident Investigation Bureau (AIB), Mr Akin Olateru has  implored all aviation stakeholders in Nigeria to work together and place premium on the development of human capacity which would in turn yield a positive level of productivity. Speaking  at the 47th Annual General Meeting of the Nigerian Air Traffic Controllers Association (NATCA) in Lagos on Saturday, he said  the aviation sector had recorded no major air crash for over three years because of the synergy and effective collaboration among the agencies.